        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Well, sailed in the direction of \"don't use hyphens in language names\"... As the validation regex is a security feature (avoid malicious codeblock annotations to load arbitrary binary payloads), it should remain as strict as possible. Nvim definitely only uses underscores for parser names, so allowing hyphens here would not help in itself.\n\nBut the main motivation here is specifically Markdown codeblock annotations where you would want to be more permissive in matching. So it could make sense to \"normalize\" the argument to `resolve_lang` first. (You will see that it's already converted to lower-case in one place; this could be combined.) The only issue is performance here, as string manipulation is relatively expensive in LuaJIT, and processing injections is a bottleneck for treesitter highlighting.",
