            "body": "> As the validation regex is a security feature (avoid malicious codeblock annotations to load arbitrary binary payloads), it should remain as strict as possible.\n\nmakes sense to me, happy to leave that alone.\n\n> So it could make sense to \"normalize\" the argument to `resolve_lang` first. (You will see that it's already converted to lower-case in one place; this could be combined.)\n\nAssuming you mean combined into the `resolve_lang` implementation, rather than at each callsite, right? Intending to open a PR for this, just making sure I have this right.",
