        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Assuming you mean combined into the resolve_lang implementation, rather than at each callsite, right?\n\nThat's the question, and related to my point about performance. Either move it (and the `:lower()`) into the function, or add a `sub` to where `resolve_lang` is called with the language name (the one with `:lower()`). In either case, these should be kept together and chained. Which one is preferable depends on which\n1.  works and\n2. is faster.",
